<title>HONG KONG: New World Infra mandates US$500 mln loan.</title>
<headline>New World Infra mandates US$500 mln loan.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-02-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>New World Infrastructure has mandated HSBC Investment Bank Asia and Goldman Sachs to arrange a US$500 million term loan facility, bankers said.</p>
<p>The facility has a final maturity of five years, with the first three years believed to be in the form of a revolving credit.</p>
<p>Bankers said that with fees the all-in return for top-tier managers is below 100 basis points.</p>
<p>Parties to the transaction were not immediately available for comment.</p>
<p>--Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2847 4039</p>
